narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Since it's independent, it depends on your PI-- I worked with Professor Shu Hu and his post-grad on a project involving quantum dots and LEDs, so I learned a lot about how they work and how to prepare them for use.
I gained a greater familiarity with tools to design PCBs like Multisim and Ultiboard, and I learned a lot about programming in C++ and working with the PSoC framework.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! Doing independent research/project with a professor is awesome! You get a lot of one-on-one teaching and feedback, and it's a good taste test of graduate school.
Yes, it's a great way to get a credit while working stuff specific to your interests.
Absolutely, it is a great way to get lab experience. You will learn a lot from the graduate students and professors that you work with.
